turnkey-mongodb-15.0 (1) turnkey; urgency=low

  * Install latest Debian Stretch MongoDB package

  * Remove RockMongo (webUI) as not supported by PHP7.0 and hasn't had update
    for years. Currently shipping with no UI.

  * Include Python3 bindings and iPython3 only (default py2 support removed).

  * Include mongo-tools (Debian package).

  * Update to mongodb PHP driver (supports PHP7.0+).

  * Use Nginx web server (replaces LigHTTPd) and provide landing page (aka
    tklweb-cp) with links to UIs.

  * Note: Please refer to turnkey-core's changelog for changes common to all
    appliances. Here we only describe changes specific to this appliance.

 -- Stefan Davis <stefan@turnkeylinux.org>  Tue, 11 Sep 2018 14:12:16 +1000

