turnkey-mongodb-12.0 (1) turnkey; urgency=low

  * Initial public release of TurnKey MongoDB.

  * Set MongoDB admin password on firstboot (convenience, security).

  * MongoDB is configured with auth enabled (security).

  * MongoDB is configured to bind to all network interfaces (convenience).

  * Regenerates all secrets during installation / firstboot (security).

  * Includes MongoDB PHP bindings and RockMongo for web based
    administration (convenience). RockMongo is powered by Lighttpd
    with SSL support out-of-the-box.

  * Includes MongoDB Python bindings and iPython (convenience).

  * Major component versions

    lighttpd            1.4.28-2+squeeze1
    mongodb             1:1.4.4-3
    python-pymongo      1.7-1
    ipython             0.10-2
    rockmongo           1.1.2 (upstream archive)
        mapreduce       1.0.0 (upstream plugin archive)
        sharding        1.0.0 (upstream plugin archive)
    mongo-php driver    Downloaded 23-07-2012

  * Note: Please refer to turnkey-core's changelog for changes common to all
    appliances. Here we only describe changes specific to this appliance.

 -- Alon Swartz <alon@turnkeylinux.org>  Wed, 01 Aug 2012 08:00:00 +0200
